comments: She is very helpful and will go out of her way to help you with the papers, but ONLY if you ask. She is a bit of a scatter brain and you can get lost during her lecture. A lot of reading but only 4 pages to write. Go to conferences and show up to class and you will pass the class.
it\'s a pretty hard class. the things you get out of it are definitely beyond worth it.
very helpful!! love this teacher, one of my favorites! trys to help out each student as much as she can, will take time from herself just to help. taking her for enlish 201 =]

Class started before 7:00 a.m. which is why students didn\'t show up. She\'s boring if you\'re expecting to do no work to become a better writer. She cares about students and will do whatever she can on her part to help you succeed, making time (hours, unpaid) after class to meet with each student.

she helps well with your writing. learned my mistakes from it. as for the class, there\'s not much there. textbook reading & group assignments. most people didnt show up everyday to class. no set cirriculum for each day. writing prompts more complicated than needed. overall she\'s ok, just be ready for boredom some days.
She is a nice prof. she tries her best to teach clearly. the work load is average. if you do the work on time you\'ll pass! very fun and talkative. :] loved the class wish she taught 201

IS VERY NICE AND TRYS TO HELP YOU AS MUCH AS POSSIBLE TENDS TO SOMETIMES GO OFF SUBJECT BUT INTERSTING STILL IS VERY INTELLIGENT SOFT SPOKEN JSUT WISH SHE WERE MORE CLEAR EASY CLASS IF YOU DO ALL THE WORK
